Description: Sherd from shoulder or lower wall of pottery closed vase; slight out-turn of wall preserved at edge by the graffito; very thick wall; porous brown clay. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 643)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.105)
